sName\\\":\\\"space-y-2 \\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",\\\"0\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"skeleton h-3.5\\\",\\\"style\\\":{\\\"width\\\":\\\"100%\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",\\\"1\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"skeleton h-3.5\\\",\\\"style\\\":{\\\"width\\\":\\\"60%\\\"}}]]}]]}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",\\\"5\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"bg-ww-surface border border-ww-border rounded-[16px] overflow-hidden\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"aspect-[16/9] skeleton rounded-none\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"p-5 space-y-3\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"skeleton h-3 w-20\\\",\\\"style\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"skeleton h-5 w-4/5\\\",\\\"style\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"space-y-2 \\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",\\\"0\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"skeleton h-3.5\\\",\\\"style\\\":{\\\"width\\\":\\\"100%\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",\\\"1\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"skeleton h-3.5\\\",\\\"style\\\":{\\\"width\\\":\\\"60%\\\"}}]]}]]}]]}]]}]]}]}],[],[]],false]},null,false]},null,false],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$1\\\",\\\"h\\\",{\\\"children\\\":[null,[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$1\\\",\\\"AnjflR7mY9yVlSZ-iT6sZv\\\",{\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L11\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":\\\"$L12\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"meta\\\",null,{\\\"name\\\":\\\"next-size-adjust\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"\\\"}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L13\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":\\\"$L14\\\"}]]}],false]],\\\"m\\\":\\\"$undefined\\\",\\\"G\\\":[\\\"$15\\\",\\\"$undefined\\\"],\\\"s\\\":false,\\\"S\\\":true}\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"16:\\\"$Sreact.suspense\\\"\\n17:I[4911,[],\\\"AsyncMetadata\\\"]\\n19:I[5677,[\\\"6874\\\",\\\"static/chunks/6874-eeb4723d64d6a73b.js\\\",\\\"8443\\\",\\\"static/chunks/app/(storefront)/blog/%5Bslug%5D/page-7282383cbbbe3b04.js\\\"],\\\"ScrollReveal\\\"]\\n14:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"hidden\\\":true,\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$16\\\",null,{\\\"fallback\\\":null,\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L17\\\",null,{\\\"promise\\\":\\\"$@18\\\"}]}]}]\\n1a:Ta8c,\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"\\u003cp\\u003eWaxed canvas has been around for centuries, and for good reason. Originally developed by Scottish sailors who discovered that oiling their sails made them more water-resistant, the technique eventually moved onshore and into everyday gear. Today, waxed canvas is a favorite material among bag makers, outdoor enthusiasts, and anyone who appreciates a fabric that gets better with age.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003ch2\\u003eWhat Makes It Special\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eWaxed canvas starts as regular cotton canvas that's been treated with a wax-based coating, typically a blend of paraffin and beeswax. This coating fills the gaps between the cotton fibers, creating a water-resistant barrier while keeping the fabric breathable. Unlike synthetic waterproof fabrics, waxed canvas has a soft, slightly tacky hand feel and develops a unique patina as it ages, with creases and wear marks that tell the story of its adventures.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eThe durability is remarkable. Heavy-duty waxed canvas, typically in the twelve to eighteen ounce range, can withstand years of daily abuse. It resists abrasion, repels light rain, and shrugs off dirt. The wax finish also makes it naturally resistant to mildew, which is a huge plus for bags that spend time outdoors.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003ch2\\u003eWorking With Waxed Canvas\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eSewing waxed canvas requires a few adjustments to your normal workflow. You'll want a heavy-duty needle, usually a size sixteen or eighteen, and a walking foot or Teflon foot on your machine to prevent the waxy surface from sticking. Skip the pins and use clips instead since pin holes don't close up in waxed fabric. And forget about ironing. Heat melts the wax and ruins the finish.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eCutting is best done with a sharp rotary cutter on a self-healing mat. Mark your pattern pieces on the wrong side with chalk, never pen, as ink will bleed through the wax. When you sew, the needle will leave visible holes along the seam line, which is part of the rugged aesthetic. Embrace it.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003ch2\\u003eHow to Care for Waxed Canvas\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eCaring for waxed canvas is refreshingly simple. Brush off dirt with a stiff brush, wipe down stains with a damp cloth and mild soap, and let it air dry. Never machine wash or dry clean a waxed canvas bag because the agitation and chemicals strip the wax coating. Over time, high-wear areas will lose their wax and the fabric will lighten in color. When this happens, you can re-wax the entire piece with a bar of fabric wax and a hair dryer. It takes about twenty minutes and your bag will look brand new.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eThe patina that waxed canvas develops over time is genuinely beautiful. Each crease, scuff, and fade mark makes the piece more uniquely yours. It's one of those rare materials where aging is a feature, not a flaw.\\u003c/p\\u003e\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"b:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"min-h-screen pt-[120px] pb-24 max-md:pt-[100px] max-md:pb-16\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"max-w-[800px] mx-auto px-10 max-md:px-5\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L19\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"nav\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-ww-muted mb-8 font-head tracking-wider uppercase\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L4\\\",null,{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/blog\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"hover:text-ww-pink transition-colors\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Blog\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":\\\"/\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-ww-text truncate\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Waxed C